Gravitational radiation by pulsar NP 0532, even at best, is not expected to be as spectacular as the Weber pulses. Gold [6] and Pacini [7] have proposed that pulsars are rotating neutron stars with off-axis magnetic fields. In a neutron star the surface magnetic field can be so large (â¼1012-1013\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
